Philex Mining, South China Resources: Philippine Stocks Preview

-- B y   I a n   C .   S a y s o n
-- 
2011-03-07T01:15:30Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-07/philex-mining-south-china-resources-philippine-stocks-preview.html
Shares of the following companies
may have unusual price changes in Philippine trading. Stock
symbols are in parentheses, and prices are as of the previous
close, unless stated otherwise.  The Philippine Stock Exchange Index rose 1.3 percent to
3,882.71.    Philex Mining Corp. (PX)  : The largest Philippine metals
producer is budgeting 3 billion pesos ($69 million) for capital
expenditure this year and is “looking at other mines or
properties that it can operate as part of its strategy for
growth,” a stock-exchange filing showed. The stock rose 0.1
percent to 14.62 pesos.    South China Resources Inc. (SOC)  : The company swapped a
property for shares in its wholly-owned unit SOC Land
Development Corp., a stock exchange filing showed. The shares
are worth 312.3 million pesos, it said. SOC Land will use the
property to develop a 2 billion-peso residential project, it
said. The stock gained 0.7 percent to 1.46 pesos.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ian C. Sayson in Manila at 
 isayson@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
